        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 30 at 6:44AM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 644 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Us-180 Near The Shackelford-
Stephens County Line, or near Hubbard Creek Reservoir, moving east at
45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mccarty Lake, The Intersection Of Us-183 And Us-
283, Elbert, Lusk, Woodson, The Intersection Of Us-
283 And Ranch Road 209, Us-180 Near The Shackelford-
Stephens County Line, Fort Griffin, Ibex, and Albany.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
